  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1987-11-20", 
    "text": "Official Accountability Act of 1987 - Amends the Federal criminal code to provide criminal penalties for Government officials (including members of the armed forces and Government contractors) who commit a national security offense. (ordering or engaging in any intelligence activity which violates any statute, Executive Order, or international agreement to which the United States is a party). States that acting \"pursuant to an order of a superior\" shall not be a defense to violations of this Act. States that violators of this Act shall be ineligible for employment by the United States for 15 years."
  }, 
